Please note that even if some issues may be “benign” in a tightly controlled desktop GUI application, in the context of a wallet handling sensitive transactions they can lead to unintended behavior or security missteps. It is highly recommended to fix the integer constant/shifting, correct the scoping issue (by defining the “password” variable in an outer scope so it’s available in the call), and review the lifetime management of “this” in any asynchronous callback.

